/*
@301 = ~Greetings mortals. I apologize for interrupting your journey. But I am bound to inform you that you will now become the property of Baeloth the Entertainer. Please ready yourself for transport.~
@302 = ~Baeloth and I have already met.~
@303 = ~Transport? What are you talking about?~
@304 = ~Allow me to elucidate. My name is Baeloth, the Entertainer. I operate an establishment in which warriors wet their weapons on woesome foes, while the wealthy watch and wager. And so, everyone wins! Almost!~
@305 = ~I don't understand anything you just said.~
@306 = ~You... arrange fights? For sport?~
@307 = ~I coopt courageous champions for compelling combat against chilling creatures, to captivate crowds!~
@308 = ~Uh, one more time please.~
@309 = ~I arrange fights for sport.~
@310 = ~Ah, our convoluted conversationalist commences to comprehend. That's swell.~
@311 = ~I suppose we may have met before, but now we have business together!~
@312 = ~You see, you have been brought to my attention as a potential player, with budding brawniness, fallow flair, quiescient capacity. To be honest, I don't quite see it. But hey, why not. My customers love nothing better than an unimpressive underdog who transcends my tests to triumph! Or, nearly so!~
@313 = ~So why don't you come on down (to the Underdark)! You are the next contestants in the fight for life, in the Black Pits!~
@314 = ~I don't have time for this. I am not going anywhere with you, I need to get to Baldur's Gate.~
@315 = ~Baeloth, you and your companion are no doubt powerful. But I have business to attend to. Perhaps a monetary donation would help you see your way to harassing someone else?~
@316 = ~Ah! I see. You still don't understand. Your business means bubkus. Your interests, in vain. Hope for your future: futile! You have been chosen. You are coming with us. End of story. This conversation is just me being polite. And honestly, I don't much enjoy being polite.~
@317 = ~You want to see me fight, then? I have fought many, and I am still here. I'll fight you and your genie, and ~
@318 = ~Listen, Baeloth, I don't know who you think you have ambushed. But I am not mere mortal surfacer to be kidnapped on a whim. The blood of a god runs my veins - and not a nice god, but the god of murder. Prophecy says I will fight on the Sword Coast - not in some squalid arena in the Underdark. Maybe you can overpower me now - fine. But you will be crossing not just me, but divine destiny. I will do everything in my power, as long as I live and maybe a good while after, to tear down everything you have, everything you are. Maybe you will gain some short-lived wealth, but in the end you will be humiliated and destroyed. The very heavens will see to it. It is not in your interest to take this risk. Walk away now, and I will forget we met this day.~
@319 = ~~
@320 = ~~
