//
// ambush scene - Baeloth not in party
//
@300 = ~Najim~
@301 = ~Greetings mortals. I apologize for interrupting your journey. But I am bound to inform you that you will now be bound to the will of Baeloth the Entertainer. Please ready yourself for transport.~
@302 = ~Baeloth and I have already met.~
@303 = ~Transport? What are you talking about?~
@304 = ~Good aft- er, I'm not sure what you call this. You surfacers' obsession with the time of day is endearingly imbecilic. Good whatever time this is. Please pardon the my familiar's direct demeanor. You are <CHARNAME>, yes? Someone is proposing a pretty price for your pelt. Though I must say, you don't look very impressive.~
@305 = ~You are late to the party, Baeloth. I already know it was Sarevok who has been hiring assassins to chase me. More importantly, none has been successful. Try to take me out, and you will end up like them.~
@306 = ~Oh? I must say, I don't care much who sets the price. I just notice what circulates in certain circles of nasty ne'er-do-wells. Someone with the whole underworld after them, who can yet survive a while - these sorts of folks fit my purposes quite well. Nobody misses them; nobody to come looking. Quite well indeed.~
@307 = ~Oh but you need not worry, I am not here to collect some banal bounty or edict of assassination. In fact I have bought out your contracts - you will be molested no more by malignant murderers. Instead, I present an invitation! Instead of facing death, you will come with us, to be champions, in courageous combat against chilling creatures, to the captivation of cavernous crowds! It will be truly heroic!~
@308 = ~And THEN you will die!~
@309 = ~You want me to fight for you?~
@310 = ~I don't understand.~
@311 = ~You will come with me, to my underground arena and battle beasts for the benefit of paying patrons. There we will question your quiescent capacities, and see if you can transcend my tests and triumph! Up to a point, anyway.~
@312 = ~I am not going to do that. I need to get to Baldur's Gate.~
@313 = ~I am not going to do anything for you, drow, least of all fight for sport.~
@314 = ~Oh but you are. The deal is done, the contracts canceled. You are a wanted criminal and presumed cadaver in the catacombs under Candlekeep. Your surface life is over, but your life in the Black Pits is about to begin. It will be short, but glorious! (But also, short.) As my genie instructed, please ready yourselves - you ARE coming with us.~
@315 = ~You want to see me fight? Let's see what you are made of! I will face whatever you can throw at me - better than you have attacked me and failed. I will go through your Black Pits, and more! I am ready to fight! Let's go!~
@316 = ~You don't understand. Until recently even I didn't understand. It turns out the blood of a god runs in my veins - the god of murder, no less. Prophecy says my place is here, on the Sword Coast, and this is where I am staying. If you get in my way you will cross not just me, but destiny itself. I promise will do everything in my considerable power, as long as I live and maybe a good while after, to tear down all you have, all you are. You will be humiliated and destroyed. The very heavens will see to it. Do you comprehend? hear me when I tell you: I am NOT going to your Black Pits, and that is final.~
@317 = ~I like that enthusiasm! But please, save it for the stadium! It is cute that you want to challenge me, but as I keep trying to explain, you are not up to it. Hmm... maybe showing is better than telling. Have you ever seen what Otiluke's Resilient Sphere can do when up-cast as a 9th-level spell? Wait, do you even have metamagic yet? Oh that's right, you're about ten years too early for that. Too bad!~
@318 = ~What prophecy?! Wait - the blood of a god, you say? You mean THAT god of murder? The Bhaal one? Since when did he have any children? I didn't know the old boy got around like that...~
@319 = ~According to the prophet Alaundo, the spawn of the lord of murder are fated to come into their inherita-~
@320 = ~Oh shut up, Najim! Just, hold on for a second. This is... I did not have this information before. I am a 'risk/reward' kind of guy, you see, and this tips the scales a bit. I think, you know what, let's just forget the whole thing, shall we? My friend and I will just, ah, wander off this way, and you, well, good luck storming the Gate.~
@321 = ~Let's go Najim. NOW.~
@330 = ~Quckened, maximized, empowered...~
