@412 = ~~
@413 = ~I don't understand. I thought you were on my team. We need to go after Sarevok - I need your assistance.~
@414 = ~Sorry, I know how this looks, and... well, it is pretty much exactly how it looks. The traitorous turn of a 'til-now-trusted tactitian! Oh, my fans will eat this one up! Sorry about the whole Sarevok thing, but realistically, the guy has been several steps ahead of you for a long time. You are simply no match for him. He can have that pathetic surfacer city, and you will have a new life - brief, barbaric, but brilliant! Even if, let's not forget, quite brief! I think you will do quite well in my fighting arena.~
@415 = ~~
@416 = ~Baeloth, you know who I am now, WHAT I am. The blood of a god runs in my veins - the god of murder, no less. Prophecy says my place is here, on the Sword Coast, and this is where I am staying. If you get in my way you will cross not just me, but destiny itself. I promise will do everything in my considerable power, as long as I live and maybe a good while after, to tear down all you have, all you are. You will be humiliated and destroyed. The very heavens will see to it. Do you comprehend? hear me when I tell you: I am NOT going to your Black Pits, and that is final.~
@417 = ~~
@418 = ~But, you don't even know how to use your gifts yet. There are supposed to be scores of you - surely the prophecy won't mind if I nab one or two to the Underdark...~
@419 = ~Oh shut up, Najim! Just, just hold on for a second. This is... I didn't quite think about it from that angle. Er, okay, let's do this. Let's chalk this up to a joke in poor taste, and go on our way, yes? Let's just forget about the Black Pits. For now. I mean, uh, onward, my leader!~
@420 = ~~
@421 = ~~
@422 = ~Oh no Baeloth, it isn't that simple. You don't try to stab me in the back and then pretend nothing happened. Defend yourself!~
@423 = ~That's right Baeloth - fall in. And don't ever again forget who is in charge here.~
@424 = ~Er, yes. Najim, you are not needed at present. Run along and tend to the arena in my absence.~
@425 = ~Very well.~
